abbawallas%20also%20delivered%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695522906000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103900189%2Cimgsize-1172240.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fnoida%2Flove-letters-sorry-notes-and-grocery-lists-what-mumbai-dabbawallas-also-delivered%2Farticleshow%2F103899130.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20famous%20dabbawallas%20of%20Mumbai%2C%20known%20for%20their%20efficient%20tiffin%20delivery%20service%2C%20have%20not%20only%20delivered%20meals%20but%20also%20emotions.%20They%20have%20come%20across%20instances%20where%20love%20letters%20and%20sorry%20notes%20were%20sent%20along%20with%20the%20lunchboxes%2C%20saving%20marriages%20in%20the%20process.%20The%20dabbawalas%20have%20even%20adapted%20to%20the%20changing%20times%20by%20involving%20the%20wives%20of%20workers%20to%20prepare%20lunches.%20Despite%20facing%20challenges%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20they%20are%20upskilling%20and%20embracing%20technology%20to%20continue%20their%20business.%20Approximately%202%20lakh%20lunch%20boxes%20are%20delivered%20each%20day%20by%20the%20Mumbai%20dabbawalas.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22AYANTIKA%20PAL%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Analysis%3A%20Justin%20Trudeau's%20Calculated%20Risk%20With%20India%20Allegation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhat%20do%20leaders%20across%20the%20world%20do%20when%20facing%20the%20threat%20of%20a%20salient%20issue%20that%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20politically%20fatal%3F%20They%20look%20for%20deflection.%20R.%20Kent%20Weaver%20says%20in%20the%20Politics%20of%20Blame%20Avoidance%20that%20%26quot%3Bin%20bad%20times%20the%20economy%20becomes%20a%20salient%20issue'%20and%20politicians%20find%20ways%20to%20blunt%20its%20impact%20on%20their%20prospect%20to%20remain%20in%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20of%20last%20week%20the%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Justin%20Trudeau%2C%20seems%20to%20have%20used%20a%20universally%20tried%20and%20tested%20political%20strategy%20of%20blame%20avoidance%20quite%20deftly%20and%20steered%20clear%20of%20matters%20that%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWeeks%20before%20he%20travelled%20to%20New%20Delhi%20for%20the%20G20%20Summit%20on%20September%209%20and%2010%2C%20Trudeau%20was%20under%20intense%20political%20pressure%20at%20home.%20The%20Conservatives%20had%20been%20going%20hammer%20and%20tongs%20after%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20over%20the%20affordability%20crisis%20or%20simply%20put%2C%20food%20inflation%20in%20Canada.%20The%20Trudeau%20government%20was%20being%20criticised%20by%20the%20opposition%20for%20making%20food%20on%20the%20plate%20expensive%20when%20grocery%20chains%20were%20making%20killer%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFood%20inflation%20wasn't%20the%20only%20subject%20he%20was%20struggling%20with.%20A%20housing%20crisis%20-%20lack%20of%20inventory%20and%20high%20rentals%20-%20had%20not%20just%20started%20pinching%20the%20public%20but%20was%20set%20to%20have%20a%20snowballing%20effect%20on%20the%20economy%20at%20large.%20With%20the%20spending%20power%20of%20the%20public%20reduced%2C%20Canada%2C%20having%20avoided%20hitting%20recession%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%2C%20was%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20one%2C%20per%20economists.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMichael%20Davenport%20in%20Oxford%20Economics%20said%3A%26quot%3BAs%20of%20April%2C%20our%20Canada%20leading%20recession%20model%20(CLRM)%20suggests%20an%2084%25%20probability%20of%20a%20recession%20in%20the%20next%20two%20quarters.%20This%20is%20the%20highest%20since%201981%2C%20and%20well%20above%20the%2060%25%20threshold%20breached%20before%20four%20of%20the%20last%20five%20recessions.%20The%20CLRM%20has%20now%20been%20above%20this%20critical%20threshold%20for%20nine%20straight%20months.%20On%20average%2C%20recessions%20begin%20four%20months%20after%20our%20recession%20model%20rises%20above%2060%25%2C%20suggesting%20a%20recession%20is%20imminent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20Trudeau%20got%20ready%20for%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20sitting%20of%20September%2C%20he%20dropped%20a%20hint%20of%20countering%20the%20looming%20domestic%20challenges%20with%20an%20international%20topic.%20After%20his%20meeting%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20in%20which%20the%20Indian%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20said%20PM%20Modi%20had%20expressed%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20concerns%20about%20the%20continuing%20anti-India%20activities%20of%20extremist%20elements%20in%20Canada%26quot%3B%2C%20Trudeau%20countered%20by%20saying%20%26quot%3BDiaspora%20Canadians%20make%20up%20a%20huge%20proportion%20of%20our%20country%20and%20they%20should%20be%20able%20to%20express%20themselves%20and%20make%20their%20choices%20without%20interference%20from%20any%20of%20the%20many%20countries%20that%20we%20know%20are%20involved%20in%20interference%20challenges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInterference%20was%20the%20operative%20word%20in%20his%20statement%20in%20India%20that%20was%20carried%20forward%20a%20week%20later%20to%20the%20Canadian%20Parliament%20on%20day%20one%20-September%2018.%20It's%20a%20word%20the%20West%20has%20been%20overtly%20and%20acutely%20wary%20of%20since%20the%20US%20raised%20an%20alarm%20of%20possible%20Russian%20interference%20in%20its%202016%20presidential%20election.%20The%20word%20has%20been%20resonating%20in%20Canada%20too%20but%20in%20relation%20to%20China.%20A%20report%20called%20China%2FCanada%3A%20Interference%20in%20the%20Chinese%20Canadian%20Community%2C%20produced%20by%20the%20federal%20Intelligence%20Advisory%20Committee%2C%20has%20been%20widely%20reported%20in%20the%20Canadian%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECBC%20News%20reported%20that%20the%201986%20intelligence%20report%20%26quot%3Bhad%20warned%20that%20Beijing%20was%20using%20open%20political%20tactics%20and%20secret%20operations%20to%20influence%20and%20exploit%20the%20Chinese%20diaspora%20in%20Canada%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20revelations%20that%20had%20been%20trickling%20in%20this%20context%20had%20already%20created%20a%20sentiment%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20Canada%20must%20build%20defences%20to%20protect%20its%20sovereignty%20and%20should%20be%20vigilant%20against%20such%20attempts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBy%20raising%20allegations%20of%20%26quot%3Binterference%26quot%3B%20by%20India%2C%20Trudeau%20clubbed%20Delhi%20with%20Beijing.%20He%20escalated%20the%20charge%20and%20even%20sounded%20an%20alarm%20to%20his%20constituents%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Boutside%20threats%26quot%3B%20to%20Canada.%20With%20this%20he%20created%20an%20issue%20that%20even%20opposition%20leader%20Pierre%20Poilievre%20couldn't%20help%20but%20prioritise%20for%20the%20time%20being%20over%20the%20affordability%20crisis%20that%20he%20had%20promised%20would%20be%20top%20of%20the%20order.%20Though%20Poilievre%20said%20no%20evidence%20was%20produced%20by%20Trudeau%20in%20parliament%20to%20back%20his%20claim%2C%20he%20too%20has%20had%20to%20tread%20carefully%20as%20the%20matter%20raised%20by%20Trudeau%20involved%20the%20sovereignty%20of%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20diplomacy%2C%20an%20issue%20like%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar's%20killing%20would%20probably%20have%20been%20raised%20and%20investigated%20behind%20closed%20doors%20between%20India%20and%20Canada%20as%20long%20as%20possible.%20As%20a%20politician%2C%20Trudeau%20could%20have%20also%20made%20the%20allegation%20outside%20parliament%20so%20as%20to%20be%20held%20less%20accountable%20for%20his%20words.%20However%2C%20he%20chose%20to%20make%20the%20statement%20in%20parliament.%20This%20was%20probably%20to%20raise%20the%20stakes%20to%20a%20level%20that%20the%20subject%20would%20overshadow%20all%20others%3B%20attaching%20parliamentary%20sanctity%20makes%20it%20an%20extremely%20grave%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAny%20Prime%20Minister%20is%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20consequences%20of%20making%20such%20an%20allegation%20in%20parliament%20and%20the%20diplomatic%20fallout%2C%20and%20naturally%2C%20so%20does%20Trudeau.%20The%20allegation%20in%20parliament%20and%20the%20diplomatic%20escalation%20perhaps%20were%20all%20a%20calculated%20risk.%20What%20may%20have%20given%20him%20some%20confidence%20is%20that%20as%20it%20emerges%20the%20'Five%20Eyes'%20(US%2C%20Australia%2C%20UK%20and%20New%20Zealand%20along%20wirth%20Canada)%20were%20aware%20of%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20also%20said%20it%20will%20make%20no%20concessions%20for%20any%20country.%20American%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Jake%20Sullivan%20said%20it%20was%20a%20matter%20of%20concern%20for%20the%20US%20and%20that%20they%20would%20continue%20to%20work%20on%20the%20matter%20regardless%20of%20the%20country.%20In%20his%20exact%20quotes%20reported%20by%20Reuters%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20some%20special%20exemption%20you%20get%20for%20actions%20like%20this.%20Regardless%20of%20the%20country%2C%20we%20will%20stand%20up%20and%20defend%20our%20basic%20principles%20and%20we%20will%20also%20consult%20closely%20with%20allies%20like%20Canada%20as%20they%20pursue%20their%20law%20enforcement%20and%20diplomatic%20process.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAustralia's%20foreign%20minister%20Penny%20Wong%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20allegations%20and%20was%20asked%20by%20the%20media%20about%20concerns%20in%20Australia.%20The%20minister%20reportedly%20said%20Australia%20was%20a%20robust%20democracy%2C%20that%20the%20Indian%20diaspora%20had%20a%20range%20of%20views%20and%20that%20it%20was%20made%20clear%20in%20relation%20to%20democratic%20debate%20in%20Australia%20that%20the%20peaceful%20expression%20of%20different%20views%20is%20a%20key%20part%20of%20Australia's%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUK%20Foreign%20Secretary%20James%20Cleverly%20also%20said%20his%20government%20took%20%26quot%3Bvery%20seriously%20the%20things%20that%20Canada%20are%20saying.%26quot%3B%20Diplomatic%20relations%20between%20India%20and%20the%20UK%20had%20also%20been%20strained%20in%20March%20when%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission%20was%20attacked%20by%20pro-Khalistan%20groups.%20India%20expressed%20anger%20over%20lax%20security%20at%20India%20House%20in%20London%20and%20in%20a%20reciprocal%20measure%20reduced%20the%20security%20outside%20the%20British%20High%20Commissioner's%20residence%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20face%20of%20the%20violence%20in%20March%20and%20the%20person%20who%20tried%20to%20bring%20down%20the%20India%20tricolour%20at%20the%20High%20Commission%2C%20Avtar%20Singh%20Khanda%2C%20died%20in%20June%20at%20a%20hospital%20in%20Birmingham.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUK%20and%20Australia%20have%20also%20faced%20New%20Delhi's%20displeasure%20over%20the%20Khalistan%20referendum%20conducted%20in%20both%20these%20countries%20by%20Sikhs%20for%20Justice%2C%20an%20outfit%20banned%20by%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20the%20US%2C%20Australia%20and%20thr%20UK%20are%20all%20clearly%20increasing%20their%20engagement%20with%20India%20as%20a%20counter%20to%20China%2C%20the%20allegation%20by%20Trudeau%20should%20have%20made%20it%20inconvenient%20for%20them%20to%20be%20faced%20with%20questions%20over%20India.%20However%2C%20none%20have%20tried%20to%20brush%20aside%20Trudeau's%20claims%20because%20of%20their%20own%20stand%20in%20the%20past%20on%20alleged%20interference%20by%20various%20countries%20ranging%20from%20Russia%20to%20China.%20And%20this%20seems%20to%20have%20created%20a%20safe%20zone%20for%20Trudeau%20to%20operate%20from%20while%20facing%20challenges%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Maha%20Siddiqui%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20has%20extensively%20reported%20on%20public%20policy%20and%20global%20affairs.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695522720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvi