20terrorism%20in%20%E2%80%9Call%20its%20forms%20and%20manifestations%E2%80%9D%20and%20called%20for%20adhering%20to%20UNCLOS%20in%20addressing%20%E2%80%9Cmaritime%20claims%E2%80%9D%20in%20South%20and%20East%20China%20seas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20UN%20general%20assembly%2C%20the%20foreign%20ministers%20of%20India%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Japan%20and%20Australia%20met%20on%20Friday%20and%20issued%20a%20joint%20readout%2C%20which%20reiterated%20their%20commitments%20on%20a%20range%20of%20issues%20from%20Indo-Pacific%20to%20terrorism%20and%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20was%20represented%20by%20External%20Affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%2C%20who%20arrived%20in%20New%20York%20on%20Friday%20to%20kick-start%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37143%2FVisit_of_External_Affairs_Minister_to_the_United_States_of_America_September_2230_2023%5C%22%3Eweek%20of%20meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20annual%20jamboree.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fbilateral-documents.htm%3Fdtl%2F37144%2FJoint_Readout_of_the_Quad_Foreign_Ministers_Meeting%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20the%20joint%20readout%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Quad%20ministers%20reaffirmed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cinternational%20law%2C%20respect%20for%20sovereignty%20and%20territorial%20integrity%2C%20and%20the%20maintenance%20of%20peace%20and%20security%20in%20the%20maritime%20domain%20underpin%20the%20development%20and%20prosperity%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECalling%20for%20disputes%20to%20be%20resolved%20peacefully%2C%20the%20Quad%20reiterated%20the%20importance%20of%20adhering%20to%20the%20UN%20Convention%20on%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20Sea%20(UNCLOS)%20to%20address%20maritime%20claims%20in%20the%20South%20And%20East%20China%20Seas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20emphasise%20the%20importance%20of%20adherence%20to%20international%20law%2C%20particularly%20as%20reflected%20in%20the%20United%20Nations%20Convention%20on%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20Sea%20(UNCLOS)%2C%20to%20address%20challenges%20to%20the%20global%20maritime%20rules-based%20order%2C%20including%20with%20respect%20to%20maritime%20claims%2C%20and%20in%20the%20South%20and%20East%20China%20Seas.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20sentence%20is%20nearly%20identical%20to%20the%20one%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2023%2F05%2F20%2Fquad-leaders-joint-statement%2F%5C%22%3EQuad%20Leaders%20joint%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20May%2C%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20the%20newly%20introduced%20term%20%E2%80%9Cincluding%20with%20respect%20to%20maritime%20claims%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffor-the-first-time-india-calls-for-abiding-by-the-2016-arbitral-award-on-south-china-sea%5C%22%3EEarlier%20in%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%20has%20changed%20its%20position%20and%20called%20for%20abiding%20by%20the%20Arbitral%20Tribunal%E2%80%99s%202016%20order%20that%20had%20struck%20down%20China%E2%80%99s%20territorial%20claims%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea.%20The%20Arbitral%20Tribunal%20was%20set%20up%20as%20per%20provisions%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fdepts%2Flos%2Fconvention_agreements%2Ftexts%2Funclos%2Fannex7.htm%5C%22%3EUNCLOS%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20change%20in%20posture%20was%20mentioned%20in%20the%20India-Philippines%20joint%20statement%20issued%20after%20the%20meeting%20of%20the%20fifth%20Joint%20Commission%20on%20bilateral%20cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20joint%20press%20release%20also%20said%20that%20the%20group%20is%20%E2%80%9Ccommitted%20to%20countering%20terrorism%20in%20all%20its%20forms%20and%20manifestations%2C%20including%20preventing%20the%20international%20and%20cross%20border%20movement%20of%20terrorists%2C%20and%20countering%20terror%20finance%20networks%20and%20safe%20havens%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the